timeAtRisks.description: TAR 1: Primary on-treatment analysis with specific gap logic (DOACs: 3-day gap + 5 days appended; Warfarin: 7-day gap + 5 days appended)

timeAtRisks.description: TAR 1: The time-at-risk period began with medication initiation until the end of continuous drug exposure, defined as a gap in exposure of more than 30 days or the end of the continuous observation period.

psSettings.description: PS Settings 1: Patients in each target and comparator exposure comparison (eg, semaglutide vs dulaglutide) were matched 1:1 using propensity scores
